plt.figure(figsize=(13,9))

#question2...Plot Total Sales Per Month for Year 2011 as Bar Chart. Is Bar Chart Better to visualize than Simple Plot?
plt.figure(figsize=(12,7))
plt.bar(df_2011_month.index,df_2011_month.values,color="r",edgecolor="k",label="Sales Month wise",width=0.5,linewidth=3)
plt.title("Sales data per month",color="y",fontsize=30)
plt.xlabel("Month no",color="b",fontsize=30)
plt.ylabel("Sles in Euro",color="g",fontsize=30)
plt.legend()
plt.show()
print("Yes Bar plot is better way to visualize our data compare than simple plot")

Yes Bar plot is better way to visualize our data compare than simple plot
